the operating loss of
$724 million in 2004 was driven by after-tax unfavorable prior year reserve development of $1.03 billion ($1.59 billion, pretax) including $500 million and $300 million (pretax) of net unfavorable prior year loss development related to the
construction and surety reserves, respectively, acquired in
table of contents
